ISLAMABAD, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan on Friday reported 208 new COVID-19 cases and one more death, the country's ministry of health said on Saturday. According to the data released by the ministry, the country's overall tally of COVID-19 cases has risen to 1,525,181, including 1,485,996 recoveries. There are 8,825 active cases in the country, including 374 patients in critical condition. The ministry added that another person died from COVID-19 on Friday, bringing the death toll to 30,360. Pakistan's southern Sindh province is the most affected region in terms of the number of cases, with 575,473 infections, followed by the eastern Punjab province which has reported 505,087 cases.  â– 